# CI/CD — Azure DevOps Pipelines

This directory contains Azure DevOps pipeline definitions for validating and deploying your agent project as a Databricks Asset Bundle.

## Pipelines

| File | Trigger | What it does |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `deploy-cicd.yml` | Manual | Generates project-specific pipeline files. Run once per project. |
| `{{ .input_project_name }}-bundle-cicd.yml` | PR to `main`, merge to `main`, merge to `release` | Validates bundle config (CI), deploys to staging (CD on main merge), deploys to prod (CD on release merge) |
| `{{ .input_project_name }}-tests-ci.yml` | PR to `main` | Runs unit and integration tests |

## Setup

1. Create service principals for staging and prod workspaces
2. Create a variable group with the required secrets (see [AgentOps Setup Guide](../../docs/agentops-setup.md))
3. Create Azure Pipelines for each YAML file using "Existing Azure Pipelines YAML file"
4. Set build validation branch policies for the `main` branch
5. Run `deploy-cicd.yml` to generate the project pipelines

## Pipeline flow

```
PR to main  →  validate bundle (staging + prod) + run tests
Merge to main  →  deploy to staging
Merge to release  →  deploy to prod
```

For details, see the [AgentOps Setup Guide](../../docs/agentops-setup.md).
